<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?><!DOCTYPE collection SYSTEM 'BioC.dtd'><collection><source>PubTator</source><date></date><key>BioC.key</key><document><id>10205272</id><passage><infon key="journal">Am. J. Hum. Genet.; 1999 May; 64(5) 1400-5</infon><infon key="year">1999</infon><infon key="article-id_pmc">PMC1377877</infon><infon key="type">title</infon><infon key="authors">Waisfisz Q, Saar K, Morgan NV, Altay C, Leegwater PA, de Winter JP, Komatsu K, Evans GR, Wegner RD, Reis A, Joenje H, Arwert F, Mathew CG, Pronk JC, Digweed M</infon><offset>0</offset><text>The Fanconi anemia group E gene, FANCE, maps to chromosome 6p.</text><annotation id="2"><infon key="identifier">MESH:D005199</infon><infon key="type">Disease</infon><location offset="4" length="14"/><text>Fanconi anemia</text></annotation><annotation id="3"><infon key="identifier">2178</infon><infon key="type">Gene</infon><infon key="NCBI Homologene">11066</infon><location offset="33" length="5"/><text>FANCE</text></annotation></passage><passage><infon key="type">abstract</infon><offset>63</offset><text>Fanconi anemia (FA) is a genetically heterogeneous autosomal recessive disease with bone marrow failure and predisposition to cancer as major features, often accompanied by developmental anomalies. The cells of patients with FA are hypersensitive to DNA cross-linking agents in terms of cell survival and chromosomal breakage. Of the eight complementation groups (FA-A to FA-H) distinguished thus far by cell fusion studies, the genes for three-FANCA, FANCC, and FANCG-have been identified, and the FANCD gene has been localized to chromosome 3p22-26. We report here the use of homozygosity mapping and genetic linkage analysis to map a fifth distinct genetic locus for FA. DNA from three families was assigned to group FA-E by cell fusion and complementation analysis and was then used to localize the FANCE gene to chromosome 6p21-22 in an 18.2-cM region flanked by markers D6S422 and D6S1610. This study shows that data from even a small number of families can be successfully used to map a gene for a genetically heterogeneous disorder.</text><annotation id="18"><infon key="identifier">MESH:D005199</infon><infon key="type">Disease</infon><location offset="63" length="14"/><text>Fanconi anemia</text></annotation><annotation id="19"><infon key="identifier">MESH:D030342</infon><infon key="type">Disease</infon><location offset="114" length="27"/><text>autosomal recessive disease</text></annotation><annotation id="20"><infon key="identifier">MESH:D000080983</infon><infon key="type">Disease</infon><location offset="147" length="19"/><text>bone marrow failure</text></annotation><annotation id="21"><infon key="identifier">MESH:D009369</infon><infon key="type">Disease</infon><location offset="189" length="6"/><text>cancer</text></annotation><annotation id="22"><infon key="identifier">MESH:D000014</infon><infon key="type">Disease</infon><location offset="236" length="23"/><text>developmental anomalies</text></annotation><annotation id="23"><infon key="identifier">9606</infon><infon key="type">Species</infon><location offset="274" length="8"/><text>patients</text></annotation><annotation id="24"><infon key="identifier">MESH:D004342</infon><infon key="type">Disease</infon><location offset="295" length="14"/><text>hypersensitive</text></annotation><annotation id="25"><infon key="identifier">2175</infon><infon key="type">Gene</infon><infon key="NCBI Homologene">108</infon><location offset="427" length="4"/><text>FA-A</text></annotation><annotation id="26"><infon key="identifier">2184</infon><infon key="type">Gene</infon><infon key="NCBI Homologene">110</infon><location offset="435" length="4"/><text>FA-H</text></annotation><annotation id="27"><infon key="identifier">2175</infon><infon key="type">Gene</infon><infon key="NCBI Homologene">108</infon><location offset="508" length="5"/><text>FANCA</text></annotation><annotation id="28"><infon key="identifier">2176</infon><infon key="type">Gene</infon><infon key="NCBI Homologene">109</infon><location offset="515" length="5"/><text>FANCC</text></annotation><annotation id="29"><infon key="identifier">2189</infon><infon key="type">Gene</infon><infon key="NCBI Homologene">3402</infon><location offset="526" length="5"/><text>FANCG</text></annotation><annotation id="30"><infon key="identifier">675</infon><infon key="type">Gene</infon><infon key="NCBI Homologene">41</infon><location offset="562" length="5"/><text>FANCD</text></annotation><annotation id="31"><infon key="identifier">2178</infon><infon key="type">Gene</infon><infon key="NCBI Homologene">11066</infon><location offset="866" length="5"/><text>FANCE</text></annotation></passage></document></collection>